      "name": "Experimental validation against FDA pump hemolysis data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis compared against published FDA experimental measurements across all 5 flow-speed operating points. RH < 1 for all conditions; mean absolute error 8.3%. Validation activities conducted at conditions representative of the COU."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-uq-campaign",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Uncertainty quantification campaign — parameter sensitivity",
      "description": "A structured UQ campaign was executed spanning inlet flow rate (±15%), rotational speed (±10%), and dynamic viscosity (±8%) using a Latin hypercube sample of 120 CFD runs. Total output variance in hemolysis index was dominated by rotational speed (Sobol index 0.61) and flow rate (0.29). The UQ campaign results confirm that the model response is well-characterised across the plausible input space and that the acceptance criterion RH < 1 is maintained with 94% probability under combined parameter uncertainty. These findings were reviewed by the credibility assessment team and informed the overall Medium assurance level determination."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-04-code-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Manufactured solution verification — Navier-Stokes solver",
      "description": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to confirm second-order spatial convergence of the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. L2 norm of velocity error scales as O(h^1.97), confirming implementation correctness."
    }
